UML:ClassifierRole.name: Communication between users and service providers

UML:TaggedValue.value:
System will allow communication and feedback process between users and service providers
  • Feedback from users to service providers: through service feedback (11.1)
  • Feedback from users to groups: through service feedback (11.1) or directly group feedback
  • Service providers will communicate with their customers using uStore

For every service will exist feedback mechanism that includes reviews, ratings & rankings, questions/answers, bugs, satisfaction, proposal of new feature etc.
  • Every one of the roles will add new feedback
  • All involved people (that uploaded the service or configured to be notified) will receive a notification about the feedback

uStore will provide a Quality Assurance process
    • AAL services will be tested with the Conformance Tools developed within Task 3.3
  • AAL services will be confirmed manually by administrators or trusted reviewers
uStore will allow all users to write a feedback about the uStore itself

uStore will serve AAL Developer Community
  • Feedback from users to developers: through service feedback (11.1)
  • Developers will communicate with their customers using uStore
  • If the service was uploaded from develop depot, develop depot will allow reading the feedback directly from the develop depot

uStore will serve AAL User Community
  • Feedback for every service provider/developer will be given by users
  • Other users will see the feedback
uStore will allow any user to propose new applications/services and to make a discussion on new ideas by all roles

uStore will manage groups. Every group will include any kind of users.
  • Group will not do any uploads/downloads directly, only users inside the group will log-in to uStore
  • In every group will exist at least one group admin user that have the permissions to add/delete other group mates
  • Group profile will include general information about the group

uStore will allow the user to subscribe to AAL Services or categories and be notified when new AAL Services or updates are available 1.10.1 uStore will allow users to enable automatic update for installed software and notification alert (as windows update). Update can require a fee; in such case the update will always be optional. 1.10.2 uStore will allow users to subscribe for news on available AAL Services or updates (like RSS feed)

System will save user profile
  • uStore saves user profile
  • Profile includes:
    • Username and password
    • Roles (Same user will behave as few roles)
      • Administrator
      • Service providers
      • Developers
      • User. Will include also type of user: End-User, Relative etc
    • Zero or more groups that the user belongs to and is he group admin user there
    • General information about the user (how will be contacted, who is he, geographic location, specific data per role: what are user's needs, what are his handicaps (e.g. blind), what are provider's abilities, what business models are supported by provider etc.)
    • History of previous orders, uploads and contracts the user signed
    • Connection to existing AAL platform profiles uploaded to uStore
      • including access permission
      • If not selected, will be filled manually by user: hardware platform, software that is already installed etc.
    • Saved items that the user is interested to order later
  • Same username/password are used in other uStores and develop depots
    • Identity management, e.g. using open ID
    • On the web it can be single entry point for several uStores and develop depots
Open issues: 1)Maybe to define general relationship concept and build all relationship between 2 different roles on top of it? 2)Babak is not sure we need developer role. To make a discussion. 3)Maybe to convert types of end-user to sub-roles or roles and then will have influence on the view (kind of personalization of uStore)

uStore will support at least 4 kinds of roles: administrators, service providers, developers and users.
Open issue: Maybe to add additional one for role with legal responsibilities or this is same role as administrator?

System will interact with AAL platform profile
  • AAL platform profile includes:
    • Hardware platform
    • Software that is already installed
    • Configuration and personalization
  • As default, AAL platform profile is saved on the user's platform
  • It will be uploaded (for backup and better search) to uStore after receiving permission from the user
    • Should be defined interface between uStore and AAL platform for this interaction
    • Automatic update mechanism without interaction from the user side (after once defining necessary permissions)
    • Automatic association with user profile
  • It will be used by uStore search engine without saving for future use (only for specific session/search)
  • The rule about platform profile will be: reuse the data as much as possible and don't bother user with same questions
System will require that during the registration every user of the uStore will fill questionnaire for filling his user profile

Search engine will allow search for any service
  • If the service is included in other service, it will be shown to user as an option
Search engine will support text based search (like Google)

Search will be allowed to be done by registered users and visitors 3.1.1 Registered used will have capability (manually or automatically) to update the uStore with AAL services/platforms installed on their personal stations and this information will be saved for future usage (by AAL platform profile) 3.1.2 Search engine will allow looking for updates on already installed software

Search engine will be user’s context aware 3.4.1 Search engine will at least allow searches based on the user's, or another, explicitly specified, geographic location 3.4.2 Search engine will rank higher AAL services which configured with the same language as the user
The searches, being a resource consuming tasks, will be protected from flooding

Uploading of AAL services will be allowed for service providers and developers roles
  • Developers will be allowed to upload software directly from depot server or client (by using artifact's meta data & additional meta data from developer).   • Developers will provide software that was not developed using develop depot
  • Service providers will provide all kinds of services
  • Uploaded service will be associated with a group and/or users (as selected by user during uploading process)
